title: 820-3536 No video output.
message: All voltages are present except Thunderbolt. No video out through external or screen. Fan spins. CPU is on and warm. Everything seems good like it should be booting. No voltage going to display connector. Unfortunately I have no info on the board. I'm pretty sure it's a spill but there's no sign of damage anywhere. No sign of life if I plug a USB drive in. No lights. Not sure where to go next.

title: 820-3536 No video output.
message: Just saw that PP3V3_S0 is reading .020 in diode mode. 3.3V is measured though.

title: 820-3536 No video output.
message: Did you wait for the board to discharge before measuring PP3V3_S0? What is resistance to GND on this bus in Ohm?

title: 820-3536 No video output.
message: It's at 24Ω. That number seems stable. Not moving at all. On a good board I'm seeing something in the range of 2.4kΩ.

title: 820-3536 No video output.
message: Well something is wrong on that bus, but EVERYTHING is on that bus. 24 Ohm is also not enough to heat something up. If you have no clue as to how this happened I'm afraid this board is a no fix.
